800-03-002	ECSO SDP Review Criteria	
The following criteria is reviewed against and enforced by ECSO during ARG Design Review, as well as re-validated for ARG Production Readiness Review:

Information Security (IS) Standards Non-Conformance: Non-conformance with IS Standards must be documented as a Security Exception per IS Standard through the Information Security Standard Exception process. For example, all violations of the IS Identity and Access Management (IAM) Standards would be submitted under a single security exception for that standard.
Section 2.2 Physical Architecture: This section must be completed in accordance with the following requirements:
A current Physical Architecture Diagram must be included at a high enough graphic resolution to make all components readable.
All connector lines must have a clear port, protocol, and authentication method label, including clear indication whether the protocol is using Bank-approved encryption.
All integrations from section 5 must be represented, except where the integration mechanism is not a straight passthrough (eg, proxy or gateway) and terminates the connection (eg, Sterling, MQ, Kafka), which would then be the integration point represented in the diagram.
Section 2.10.1 Firewall Rules: This section is slated for removal and will no longer be reviewed or validated.
Section 2.10.2.1 User Base, Access, Roles and Provisioning: This section must clearly document:
What identity provider (IdP) is in use,
Whether SSO is being implemented,
Explicit details about provisioning of users (eg, use of UAP/Sailpoint, manual processes),
If MFA is being implemented,
What roles are being supported,
If any of those roles constitute privileged access, and
If privileged access, then is it implemented in accordance with Privileged Access Management (PAM) requirements.
Section 2.10.2.2 Authentication and Authorization: This section is slated for removal and will no longer be reviewed or validated. All User IAM, IGA, and PAM descriptions must be added to Section 2.10.2.1.
Section 2.10.2.3 Service Accounts: This section must be completed for all Non-Human Access (e.g., service account, API client credential, AWS IAM Role, Azure/M365 Service Principal, etc.) used by the solution including a statement attesting to meeting Service Account management requirements (eg, vaulting in an ECSO-approved PAM solution).
Section 2.10.3 Digital Certificates: All digital certificates managed by the product team must be fully documented.
Section 2.10.4 Data: The highest data classification must be represented. Any privacy, industry, and/or regulatory compliance requirements must be listed.
Section 2.11 Exceptions and Deviations: All Exceptions, SIIs, and Observations must be listed with pertinent metadata, which includes the ID, a short description, and the status and disposition of the request. Any Security Exceptions that are denied will be grounds for Security voting "Not Approved."
Section 6.6.1 Logging: Security event logging must be implemented in accordance with the Information Security Logging and Monitoring Standards.
