800-04-001	ECSO Enterprise IAM Criteria	
SSO Integration Requirement: Integration with a Bank-approved Single Sign-On (SSO) provider is a non-functional requirement for all new projects.
If a service is net-new and SSO integration is supported, then SSO integration must be implemented.
If a service is existing and SSO integration is supported, then SSO integration should be pursued at the earliest opportunity.
Preferred IDP: Okta is the preferred SSO identity provider and should be used in lieu of other options.
Enterprise SSO Okta Protocol Requirement: Information systems must integrate with the Bank's Okta ESSO using SAML 2.0 or OIDC/Oauth2.
Deprecated IDP: No new integrations with Ping One will be supported for SSO. Okta must be used instead.
Limits on AD for SSO: FCB AD integration for internal SSO purposes is only permissible with Integrated Windows Authentication (IWA) using Kerberos (primary) or NTLMv2 (if Kerberos is not available), and only if Okta integration is not possible. LSVB AD integration is deprecated and not permissible. Other legacy protocol support may be permitted at the express permission of the IAM control owner, and only for the minimum duration necessary to facilitate upgrading to modern protocols.
MFA Is Not Transitive: MFA must occur at the point of login. Implied MFA via Zscaler does not meet this requirement, but proxied access via Cyberark (PAM) does.
PAM Requirement: All privileged account credentials must be vaulted in PAM.

