800-05-002	API Data Protection Criteria	
Transport Encryption: Network protocols used to access Bank APIs must implement Bank-approved encryption (e.g., TLS 1.2+ using HTTPS). 
Protect Sensitive Data: Confidential and Restricted data must not be passed in an unsafe manner.
Payload Protection: Data payload (eg, request, response) integrity should be evaluated through cryptographic mechanisms (eg, HMAC).
