800-05-005	API Authorization Criteria	
The following authorization criteria must be met in API/Middleware implementations:

All API calls must be properly authorized in accordance with this TUG and the IS Standards (no implicit trust).
All access provided by APIs must apply the principle of least privilege, ensuring the minimum functional and data exposure required for the designed API function.
Authorization rules must be designed for all levels, including objects, object properties, functions, business flows, and data.
Authorization servers must associate access tokens with certain resource servers and actions on that resource server.
Authorization checks for user attributes (eg, job code, department), user groups, and user roles must be implemented where possible.
