800-05-007	API Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) Configuration Criteria	
CORS requests must only be allowed from trusted domains. Servers must validate the Origin header and only allow requests from trusted domains 
The Access-Control-Allow-Origin header specifies which domains can access the server’s resources. It must be set to a specific domain or a list of domains, rather than using the wildcard character “*”. 
CORS must only be enabled for the necessary resources and not for the entire server. This helps limit the attack surface and reduce the potential for security vulnerabilities. 
Access-Control-Allow-Headers must contain a list of headers and not “*”.  
Access-Control-Allow-Methods must contain a list of HTTP methods and not “*”.
The Access-Control-Allow-Credentials header specifies whether the server allows cookies or other credentials to be sent with CORS requests. This must only be set to “true” if the server needs to receive cookies or other credentials from the requesting domain. 
